default              
defaultMr Timpson:default It is more to do with the way that planning is decided. Because of its dry approach, if you like, and its set criteria—we see in our own constituencies with other planning applications that people raise quite emotive issues about the effect something will have on their lives—many of those considerations are not part of the criteria when it comes to planning. We have looked at this. I am happy, as was set out in the debates that we have already had in Parliament on this issue, to write in some detail about the specific difficulties with the planning system.
